verbatimAttributes: Shrubs ~2m tall. Female plant. Branches dark red-purple, waxy. Catkins precocious, not on leafy shoots, 3-4cm long. Capsules short, silky. Floral bracts dark purple-brown, long-hairy. Leaves glabrous, elliptic to narrowly oblanceolate, entire, acute, 4-5cm x 1.5-2cm. Petioles 5-6mm. Dominant willow at this locality.

habitat: Rocky slopes.
verbatimAttributes: Low shrub with dark, reddish-purple, glabrous twigs. Catkins precocious, not of leafy branches, relatively large, ~3cm. Capsules short-hairy with long, narrow, blackish and densely hairy bracts. Leaves up to 3cm long, with reddish petioles, glaucous below, dark green above. Sparse hairs on lower leaf surface. Leaves ~planar, not revolute, Lance elliptic with acute tips.
